PagineGialle,Hotel/B&B,Como,B&B Antico Chiostro,"Via Lambertenghi, 4 - 22100 Como (CO)",031 241356,https://conventosantantonio.it/en,"[Home En] | Home En Skip to main content B&B Convento Sant' Antonio B&B Convento Sant' Antonio Access to the Rooms The rooms are located on the third floor with no elevator access . The property is a historic 14th-century building and does not have a lift. We kindly ask guests to take this into consideration when making their reservation. Our rooms Find out more Room Liz Explore the Room Room Greta Explore the Room Room Sofia Explore the Room Our Story In the historic heart of Como, just a few steps from the lake, B&B Convento Sant’Antonio is set within a former 14th-century monastery. A place rich in history, now transformed into a welcoming home where the charm of the past meets modern comfort. Surrounded by centuries-old walls, parquet floors, and peaceful atmospheres, Convento Sant’Antonio is the perfect starting point for exploring Como on foot, experiencing the lake, and savoring the city’s authentic way of life. About Us Our Team B&B Convento Sant’Antonio is, above all, about people and smiles. Giampiero, the owner of the property, welcomes guests with passion and care, together with Marinella, who supports him in greeting guests and looking after the Convent each day. Making every morning special is Shana: with her kindness, contagious cheerfulness, and ever-present smile, she takes care of breakfast and room cleaning, creating a warm and welcoming atmosphere every day. Contact us Useful Information Frequently Asked Questions Is parking available at the property? Yes, B&B Convento Sant’Antonio offers a private inner courtyard with parking spaces reserved for guests. The parking service is available at a rate of €15 per day. Is breakfast included in the stay? Yes, breakfast is included in your stay. We offer a rich and varied selection featuring fresh fruit, yogurt, cereals, croissants, bread, and eggs freshly prepared by our team according to each guest’s preferences. Fruit juices, tea, coffee, and cappuccino are also available to help you start your day in the best pos",
