PagineGialle,Hotel/B&B,Como,Suites & Atelier Lake Como,"Lungo Lario Trento, 56 - 22100 Como (CO)",349 7940744,https://suiteslakecomo.com/en/,"[Suites & Atelier Lake Como – Luxury suites in Como] | Discover Suites & Atelier Lake Como. Exclusive suites in the heart of Como, timeless elegance, and an unforgettable stay on Lake Como. | Suites & Atelier Lake Como – Luxury suites in Como Skip to content Live the magic of an enchanted place on Lake Como. SUITES ATELIER Suites & Atelier Lake Como Amm_SlC 2025-10-16T15:36:38+02:00 DISCOVER THE SUITES The journey starts! Suite Tropicale 1 Light filtering in from exotic worlds view Suite Coloniale 2 Deams and visions of distant journeys view Suite Palme 3 In the shadow of large, silent leaves view Suite Chinoiserie 4 Precious designs in rarefied blue view Suite Floreale 5 The colourful scent of petals and flowers view Suite Leopard 6 Courious feline gaze view A magical place , where poetry is in a glance. Ready to live the dream? We welcome you to this very special hotel, former home-studio of the Como silk drawing artist Beppe Spadacini, great traveller and curious mind. The place of the heart for those who plan ever-changing itineraries, for those who take on the intimate task of constructing memories, creating experiences, noting down emotions. A travel carnet with a page always open, ready to welcome the sketch of new landscapes, the discovery of enchanting horizons and the surprise of small special details. If you recognise yourself in the idea of a soul sensitive to beauty, Suite & Atelier is the place for you: not only for the view of the waters of Lake Como, ever more desirable and exclusive, but also and above all for the enveloping atmosphere you will feel as soon as you cross the threshold. view SUITES view EVENT SPACE Transform your stay at Lake Como into a truly unique experience. Book now We welcome you to a place beyond time and space. “Lake Como is the most beautiful thing I have ever seen.” P. B. Shelley (English poet 1792 – 1822) LAKE COMO Secret places in plain sight Already in Roman times Lake Como was a holiday destination: Pliny the Younger devoted himself to otium in the residences of Lenno and Bellagio. From the 16th century, gardens and villas began to overlook the Lario, to name but a few: Villa Carlotta and its luxuriant botani",
